24:37.309 --> 24:38.310
[cracking]

24:40.770 --> 24:41.771
[grunts]

24:49.613 --> 24:50.989
Oh, God! Oh, God!

24:52.073 --> 24:54.451
[panting]

24:57.412 --> 25:00.540
We can't pull this poor girl apart
and bury her in some unmarked grave.

25:06.671 --> 25:08.715
Well, what the hell are we gonna do?

25:09.382 --> 25:11.051
This is not who we are.

25:11.134 --> 25:12.844
This is not the reason we came here.

25:14.012 --> 25:15.680
If we stray from the values
we know to be true,

25:15.764 --> 25:18.058
then everything we've created
will be destroyed.

25:18.141 --> 25:20.435
Integrity in everything we do, remember?

25:22.270 --> 25:23.980
So what do we do with the body?

25:28.360 --> 25:29.861
We give her back to her parents.

25:32.948 --> 25:34.157
And in the meantime?

25:35.075 --> 25:37.244
If the others see this,
they're gonna think I'm the killer.

25:40.455 --> 25:41.957
We'll bring her back to the shed.

25:42.707 --> 25:45.877
We wait until the police arrive.
But we do do the right thing here.

25:56.638 --> 25:58.181
[slurps]

25:58.265 --> 25:59.975
Dude, do you have to eat like that?

26:02.102 --> 26:05.105
-Eat like what? What's your problem?
-[Peter] Okay, sun's up.

26:05.188 --> 26:06.856
-Let's get going.
-[Mark] Cool your jets.

26:06.940 --> 26:08.525
Renee and Antoine aren't down yet.

26:13.405 --> 26:14.572
[Renee] Judith.

26:14.656 --> 26:16.157
Those pancakes smell divine.

26:16.241 --> 26:18.618
You guys are late. Where were you?

26:21.162 --> 26:23.957
There are no bosses here.
Stop acting like one.

26:24.833 --> 26:28.211
We were outside doing sun salutations.

26:28.295 --> 26:30.005
I do them every morning, rain or shine.

26:30.088 --> 26:32.007
I thought yoga was supposed
to make you calm.

26:32.090 --> 26:34.301
[Antoine]
Let's focus on getting to Gene's.

26:34.384 --> 26:37.679
It's 30 klicks away, which is a long walk
in sub-zero temperatures.

26:37.762 --> 26:41.683
Susan and me, we saw an old RV
out in the woods last night.

26:42.267 --> 26:43.685
Couldn't we all just climb in that
and drive out?

26:43.768 --> 26:44.894
[Glenn] It's my RV.

26:44.978 --> 26:47.814
And I'm telling you, it's not getting
ten feet in this ice and snow.

26:47.897 --> 26:49.065
Don't be a retard.

26:49.649 --> 26:51.609
You know,
we're not allowed to say that word.

26:51.693 --> 26:53.236
-You fucking retard.
-[Peter] Guys, we'll walk.

26:53.320 --> 26:54.779
[Noah] No, we won't walk, man.

26:55.447 --> 26:57.782
Exhibit A, exhibit B.

26:58.533 --> 26:59.743
You still think that's a good idea?

26:59.826 --> 27:02.495
This time, we won't be two panicked people
running through the snow.

27:03.163 --> 27:06.833
This time, we'll be a group,
with a plan, prepared.

27:06.916 --> 27:09.794
-That's not a plan. It's suicide.
-I'm sorry, you got a better idea, bud?

27:09.878 --> 27:11.671
Nope. I'm eating breakfast.

27:11.755 --> 27:13.590
[Peter] Here's the deal. Two groups.

27:14.174 --> 27:15.091
Group number one stays here.

27:15.175 --> 27:17.719
Group number two
will go on the trek with me.

27:17.802 --> 27:20.597
And I'm taking the strongest people.
Do I have any objections?

27:20.680 --> 27:23.266
-Not from me. It's a good plan.
-Yeah, I'm up for it.

27:23.350 --> 27:25.518
I can't sit around here anymore.
I'm going stir crazy.

27:25.602 --> 27:26.895
I think it's a good idea.

27:28.146 --> 27:29.856
But do you need to take
all the strongest people?

27:29.939 --> 27:31.524
We'll be like sitting ducks here.

27:31.608 --> 27:33.068
She's right. We can't all go.

27:33.151 --> 27:35.737
Oh, I'm sorry, Judith,
I wasn't thinking. I'll stay.

27:35.820 --> 27:37.113
You do what you wanna do.

27:37.655 --> 27:38.823
Let me stay.

27:38.907 --> 27:40.325
I've taken self-defense courses.

27:40.492 --> 27:41.493
[laughing]

27:42.494 --> 27:44.537
Self-defense courses.

27:44.621 --> 27:45.705
I'll stay too.

27:45.789 --> 27:49.209
[Peter] Okay, guys, guys, it's decided.

27:49.292 --> 27:50.752
You guys stay here.

27:50.835 --> 27:53.838
Renee, Dawn, Mark and Glenn,
you guys come with me.

27:54.506 --> 27:55.673
We leave in five.

27:57.425 --> 27:58.301
[Dawn] I need a minute.

28:04.224 --> 28:05.225
Antoine.

28:07.060 --> 28:08.228
You all right?

28:13.817 --> 28:14.818
I'm fine.

28:23.076 --> 28:24.077
Renee!

28:32.836 --> 28:38.007
These walkies are old,
but the range isn't half bad.

28:40.885 --> 28:44.639
Any sign of trouble,
you radio immediately.

28:46.224 --> 28:48.727
-Okay?
-You do the same.

28:49.894 --> 28:51.271
Be careful out there.

28:55.233 --> 28:57.694
[Glenn] All right. Get a room, you kids.

29:03.032 --> 29:06.161
I'm freezing my ass off.
Are you sure this is a good idea?

29:06.244 --> 29:08.329
What if they're just leading us out here
to kill us?

29:08.413 --> 29:09.706
Well, we don't let our guard down.

29:10.457 --> 29:13.042
-Well, Glenn seems pretty sketch.
-Yeah.

29:13.126 --> 29:16.212
And Mark, "Mr. Wise Man On The Hill."

29:17.630 --> 29:19.591
You know he had one of his talks
with Andy, right?

29:19.674 --> 29:22.469
Yeah, and Susan too,
and they both wound up dead.

29:22.552 --> 29:23.845
What if it's him?

29:23.928 --> 29:27.766
Let's not forget "American Gothic 2.0,"
Renee and Antoine.

29:28.308 --> 29:30.643
What are they?
Brother/wife, sister/husband?

29:30.727 --> 29:33.772
Look, if we run into any trouble,
I've got my gun back.

29:34.522 --> 29:35.356
What? How?

29:36.065 --> 29:38.860
All that matters is that I got it back,
no thanks to you.

30:58.022 --> 30:59.023
[faint growling]

30:59.941 --> 31:00.817
What is that?

31:07.240 --> 31:09.158
-Fuck, it's not there.
-What's not in there?

31:09.242 --> 31:11.452
[walkie screeches]
Renee, this is Antoine. Is that you?

31:13.121 --> 31:14.497
[walkie squelches]

31:14.831 --> 31:17.584
-Shh.
-Seriously, what the fuck is going on?

31:18.459 --> 31:20.420
-[Dawn panting]
-[growling]

31:20.503 --> 31:21.880
What the fuck?

31:24.507 --> 31:25.383
[growling]

31:35.476 --> 31:36.728
[sighs]

31:37.937 --> 31:39.188
[Mark] What? What?

31:43.943 --> 31:45.361
[Mark] What is it?

31:46.404 --> 31:47.405
I think it's a wolf.

31:50.325 --> 31:52.493
Antoine, this is Renee. We heard you.

31:53.202 --> 31:54.662
[Antoine]
Keep your eyes open.

31:54.746 --> 31:56.664
[Renee] We're okay.
We're gonna keep going.

31:57.540 --> 31:58.750
[Antoine]  Be safe.

32:04.422 --> 32:06.549
[mutters]
Yeah, sure, let's follow the fucking wolf.

32:26.653 --> 32:28.237
[gasps]

33:08.861 --> 33:10.697
[panting]

33:29.424 --> 33:31.384
-Antoine, are you there?
-[Dawn] How much farther?

33:31.467 --> 33:33.845
-I think we're almost there.
-[Renee] Antoine.

33:33.928 --> 33:35.888
Come in, Antoine.
Can you hear me? Are you there?

33:38.349 --> 33:41.269
-Maybe his battery's dead.
-[Peter] Or we're out of range.

33:41.352 --> 33:43.312
Either way, the walkie is useless.

33:49.318 --> 33:51.279
[wincing]

34:09.922 --> 34:11.132
Note to self...

34:12.341 --> 34:14.594
try not to think about how many times

34:14.677 --> 34:17.680
big Glenn abused little Glenn
on this mattress.

34:20.683 --> 34:22.060
[winces]

34:22.143 --> 34:25.063
It's better than the floor, yeah.
[groans]

34:25.563 --> 34:27.315
[grunts] Oh!

34:27.940 --> 34:29.358
Ow.

34:30.234 --> 34:31.235
[sighs]

34:33.237 --> 34:34.447
Oh--!

34:34.530 --> 34:38.785
[panting]
Ibuprofen, I'm coming at ya.

34:41.412 --> 34:42.413
Ah.

34:50.254 --> 34:52.423
Who the fuck is Benny Ironside?

35:04.310 --> 35:06.020
[panting]

35:08.314 --> 35:09.315
Guys!

35:12.819 --> 35:13.820
[group panting]

35:17.990 --> 35:19.408
[bangs]

35:21.035 --> 35:22.078
A phone.

35:24.122 --> 35:25.123
[beeps]

35:27.583 --> 35:29.710
-It's dead.
-Maybe it just needs charging.

35:30.795 --> 35:32.880
-No, the phone's plugged in.
-Then why the fuck isn't it working?

35:32.964 --> 35:35.133
-How are we supposed to know that?
-Give me the keys to the SUV.

35:35.216 --> 35:36.259
-I'm gonna start it.
-Wait.

35:38.261 --> 35:40.054
Here's your explanation.

35:40.138 --> 35:42.265
Looks like Gene wasn't very good
at paying his bills, either.

35:42.348 --> 35:44.392
Who gives a fuck about the phone?

35:44.475 --> 35:46.477
Our way out of here
is right there with the SUV.

35:51.149 --> 35:52.316
Shoot.

35:53.442 --> 35:56.112
Come on, baby. Come on, baby.
Come on, come on, come on.

35:56.195 --> 35:58.364
-[Peter] It's not turning over.
-Yeah, I got that!

35:58.447 --> 35:59.907
Thank you for the fucking update!

35:59.991 --> 36:03.077
Come on, you dirty--
Motherfucker, God damn it!

36:03.161 --> 36:06.122
Glenn!
I really don't think that's gonna help.

36:07.081 --> 36:08.124
[mutters] Fuck you.

36:08.207 --> 36:09.417
The light was left on.

36:10.084 --> 36:12.378
-What fucking light?
-This one above the mirror.

36:14.130 --> 36:16.841
[Dawn's voice]  Great. I will be in the SUV
in the meantime.

36:28.436 --> 36:30.563
Which one of you fucking idiots...?

36:30.646 --> 36:31.647
Well, I didn't--

36:32.607 --> 36:35.193
Look, I was waiting for Noah
to get me a sweater, and--

36:36.736 --> 36:37.570
[sighs]

36:37.653 --> 36:40.114
You are not the sharpest knife
in the drawer, are you?

36:40.198 --> 36:41.282
Glenn, she didn't do it on purpose.

36:41.365 --> 36:43.784
You know that?
Do you fucking know that?

36:43.868 --> 36:46.704
She brought a gun,
and now the only vehicle is disabled.

36:46.787 --> 36:50.082
You know what, Glenn?
I keep trying to remind myself

36:50.166 --> 36:53.085
to see the scared little boy
inside of you that is lashing out

36:53.169 --> 36:54.170
because he's afraid.

36:55.213 --> 36:58.341
But I really don't think
that discharging your rage

36:58.424 --> 37:01.802
and your fear on others
is of service to anyone.

37:01.886 --> 37:04.347
Don't fucking talk to me
unless you're gonna speak English.

37:04.430 --> 37:06.182
Do you fucking understand me,  Kimosabe?

37:07.266 --> 37:09.810
Can we just find something to make
this trip back a little easier?

37:09.894 --> 37:10.978
Huh?

37:11.062 --> 37:12.021
[Mark] Renee's right.

37:13.731 --> 37:14.732
Fuck.

37:19.779 --> 37:21.864
[strumming]

37:23.491 --> 37:25.952
Renee, this is Antoine. Please respond.

37:26.035 --> 37:27.787
She hasn't answered you
in a long time, Antoine.

37:27.870 --> 37:29.455
She's probably out of range.

37:30.581 --> 37:32.250
I'll check the signal in the back.

37:36.087 --> 37:37.588
This guy's gotta chill out.

37:38.714 --> 37:42.510
Antoine's trying to control a situation
that he has no actual control over.

37:44.512 --> 37:45.346
Poor guy.

37:47.682 --> 37:49.809
Thanks for the soup, Judith.
It was really good.

37:51.435 --> 37:54.355
I'm freezing, so I'm gonna go grab
some wood and start a fire.

37:54.438 --> 37:57.692
-Well, shouldn't someone go with you?
-No, it should just take a second.

37:57.775 --> 37:59.360
You don't want a hand, Keira?

37:59.860 --> 38:02.196
[door opens, closes]

38:07.118 --> 38:08.160
What about you?

38:09.787 --> 38:11.956
Could I tempt you
with some of my world famous soup?

38:12.039 --> 38:15.251
No, I'm not really
a caramelized onion guy.

38:17.336 --> 38:18.671
I'll just have my grapes.

38:23.092 --> 38:24.343
Did you get my letter?

38:28.097 --> 38:29.473
Yes, I did. Thank you.

38:30.766 --> 38:34.270
Good.
Sometimes I think it's easier for me

38:34.353 --> 38:38.566
to write these feelings down
just to get it out,

38:38.649 --> 38:40.901
um, especially in a fish bowl
like this one.

38:45.990 --> 38:47.033
I'm glad you did.

39:00.713 --> 39:02.214
[walkie squelches]

39:13.017 --> 39:14.185
Hello?

39:26.614 --> 39:27.615
[screams]

39:36.665 --> 39:37.708
[Noah] What...?

39:39.919 --> 39:40.920
Is that...?

39:42.838 --> 39:45.841
Oh, fuck, man, that is.
That's a rotten fucking severed hand.

39:45.925 --> 39:49.053
-It's Talvinder's, obviously.
-You don't know that.

39:49.136 --> 39:51.764
[yells]
No more games!

39:53.516 --> 39:55.142
You're gonna tell us
what really happened to her.

39:55.226 --> 39:57.645
-How many times I gotta do this shit?
-Until you tell us the truth!

39:57.728 --> 40:00.689
I already told you what I know.
I didn't even know Talvinder was dead.

40:00.773 --> 40:02.691
Yeah, you and your friends
probably killed her with your own hands.

40:02.775 --> 40:05.444
You guys are supposed to go, like,
"Kumbaya" and "love thy neighbor,"

40:05.528 --> 40:08.155
but all you do is hurl accusations
and blame us for shit.

40:08.239 --> 40:11.659
Yeah, because every fucking thing
that's happened in the last 24 hours

40:11.742 --> 40:13.661
has been on you and your friends.

40:13.744 --> 40:14.870
-I don't need this.
-You're not going anywhere.

40:14.954 --> 40:18.165
-Man, get the fuck out of my face.
-Start talking, you piece of shit.

40:21.293 --> 40:23.045
-[gunshot echoes]
-That was a warning shot.

40:23.129 --> 40:25.423
Next one won't be a warning.
Just try me.

40:25.506 --> 40:27.633
Just try me, man, see what happens.

40:27.716 --> 40:29.009
Stay the fuck away from me or I'll shoot.

40:29.093 --> 40:30.803
-I just wanna talk to you, man.
-[Noah] Stay away!

40:30.886 --> 40:32.763
Look, you don't need to do that, Noah.

40:32.847 --> 40:36.392
I took a vow of non-violence, all right?

40:36.475 --> 40:39.687
I'm not gonna hurt you. We all did.
We're not gonna hurt you.

40:40.896 --> 40:43.524
-We just want the truth.
-But I already told you.

40:46.402 --> 40:47.570
[grunting]

40:48.863 --> 40:50.322
[Keira] Antoine, you can let him go!

40:52.324 --> 40:53.742
You're choking him to death!

40:55.953 --> 40:57.163
Antoine, that's enough!

41:02.084 --> 41:03.335
[groans]

41:04.003 --> 41:05.171
The truth.

41:05.671 --> 41:06.714
Now!

41:06.797 --> 41:08.966
I'll tell you the truth.
It was Owen Turnbull.

41:10.885 --> 41:12.928
-Who's Owen Turnbull?
-He went to our camp, okay?

41:13.012 --> 41:15.139
He was a really creepy guy
obsessed with Talvinder.

41:15.222 --> 41:16.182
He never left her side.

41:16.265 --> 41:18.476
Okay, when Talvinder went missing,

41:18.559 --> 41:20.895
you didn't have to be fucking Sherlock
to know who did it.

41:20.978 --> 41:22.730
So you think this Owen guy killed her?

41:22.813 --> 41:26.025
Everyone did, including the cops.
They just couldn't find the body.

41:26.108 --> 41:28.944
It's been five years without an answer.

41:29.862 --> 41:32.198
We figured Owen dumped the body
somewhere in the area.

41:32.281 --> 41:33.991
We just came back to look.

41:34.575 --> 41:35.784
Why now?

41:36.410 --> 41:38.621
Why now? It's the fucking dead of winter!

41:42.458 --> 41:43.626
What the hell is going on?!

41:49.632 --> 41:51.050
[panting]

41:52.676 --> 41:53.969
[gasps]

42:08.526 --> 42:10.819
This house was supposed to be
a peaceful haven.

42:13.239 --> 42:14.698
Now it's become a war zone.

42:18.744 --> 42:22.540
It's affecting us all,
this fear and hatred and violence.

42:24.750 --> 42:26.335
Anyone can take a life...

42:28.337 --> 42:30.089
given the circumstances.

42:33.968 --> 42:35.678
I have to get rid of her body.

42:36.637 --> 42:37.721
The killer already found it.

42:37.805 --> 42:40.724
If it's not in the shed I'll keep looking,
and it goes in the lake.

42:40.808 --> 42:42.768
-I should go with you.
-No, you're exhausted.

42:42.851 --> 42:44.186
No, I'm fine.

42:45.229 --> 42:47.398
It would be less suspicious if I go alone.

42:48.023 --> 42:49.858
Besides, I won't be alone. I'll have this.

42:49.942 --> 42:52.069
-No, please let me come with you.
-No.

42:52.152 --> 42:53.988
How do we face our problems?

43:01.161 --> 43:03.080
How do we face our problems?

43:11.297 --> 43:13.215
Could I talk to you for a minute?

43:13.299 --> 43:15.759
Oh, Judith,
this isn't the best time right now.

43:15.843 --> 43:17.553
-I'm sorry.
-It won't take long.

43:22.057 --> 43:23.809
Earlier in the kitchen...

43:25.144 --> 43:28.897
I saw you.
I don't wanna say you were spying.

43:28.981 --> 43:33.110
I just-- I feel like this is...
a much bigger conversation.

43:33.193 --> 43:35.696
Maybe later you, me and Renee
can sit down and--

43:35.779 --> 43:38.032
I don't want to involve Renee.
I wanna hear from you.

43:43.078 --> 43:44.079
Okay.

43:46.749 --> 43:52.713
Listen, we're all feeling
a lot of helplessness right now.

43:52.796 --> 43:57.051
a lot of fear, and these are powerful,
powerful emotions.

43:58.510 --> 44:01.847
It can easily make us
lose our center and...

44:03.015 --> 44:07.853
cause us to do things to help us escape

44:07.936 --> 44:09.605
from the things
that are happening around us.

44:13.776 --> 44:15.653
I didn't want to embarrass you, Judith.

44:17.321 --> 44:18.656
I'm sure it's harmless.

44:21.659 --> 44:23.285
Thank you, Antoine.

44:23.369 --> 44:24.536
Thank you.

44:45.391 --> 44:47.476
Okay, you stole my gun
and now they have it again.

44:47.559 --> 44:48.894
What the hell, Noah?

44:49.520 --> 44:52.147
How else was I supposed
to defend myself in my crippled state?

44:52.231 --> 44:54.441
How do you expect anyone
to trust you when you pull this shit?

44:56.068 --> 44:57.736
You guys are just so against me.

44:57.820 --> 44:59.113
I think you always have been.

44:59.863 --> 45:02.574
You even blame me for Talvinder. Admit it.

45:07.788 --> 45:08.789
Yeah.

45:09.957 --> 45:12.918
I knew it, I knew it.
I knew you blame me.

45:13.001 --> 45:14.753
Noah, we're marked for death,

45:14.837 --> 45:16.880
so what you need to do
is stop worrying about the past

45:16.964 --> 45:18.757
and start worrying
about surviving the present.

45:18.841 --> 45:20.926
'Cause that's what this is about
right now.

45:21.009 --> 45:22.344
Survival.

45:30.894 --> 45:32.479
[whispers]
What'd you tell 'em?

45:32.563 --> 45:33.730
The official story.

45:34.898 --> 45:37.025
Crazy Owen killed her.

45:37.109 --> 45:40.737
No body was found,
and we came back here looking for answers.

45:40.821 --> 45:43.907
-Did they believe it?
-They don't believe anything we say.

45:45.284 --> 45:47.578
They hate our guts. This is war.

45:49.746 --> 45:52.624
We cannot be at war with them
if we're going to survive this.

45:56.962 --> 45:59.131
-Hey, if you're going by the kitchen--
-No.

45:59.214 --> 46:01.550
I just want a snack. I'm so hungry.

46:01.633 --> 46:02.885
[sighs]

46:37.920 --> 46:39.087
[lid thumps]

46:40.464 --> 46:41.632
No.

46:42.007 --> 46:43.425
No, no, no, no, no.

46:44.009 --> 46:45.344
No, no, no, no...

46:52.392 --> 46:53.602
[grunts]

46:54.436 --> 46:56.063
[Antoine screaming]
No! No!

46:57.272 --> 46:58.273
[groans]

47:02.694 --> 47:04.196
No! Please...!

47:04.279 --> 47:05.572
Don't...

47:05.656 --> 47:06.698
Don't!

47:07.449 --> 47:09.201
No!

47:09.451 --> 47:10.452
[screams]

47:13.455 --> 47:14.331
[Antoine screaming]

47:15.958 --> 47:18.168
-[whirrs]
-[screaming]

47:20.629 --> 47:21.838
No!

47:24.216 --> 47:25.509
[screaming]

47:32.307 --> 47:34.142
