No, you're totally right. You don't.

48:26.236 --> 48:28.280
Let's go see what Antoine
and Renee have to say

48:28.363 --> 48:30.532
about your little contraband pharmacy.

48:33.952 --> 48:34.911
It's warfarin.

48:35.495 --> 48:38.248
They use it to treat
blood clot disorders of the lungs.

48:39.666 --> 48:42.836
It's a life-saving drug, but it is
out of this world expensive, okay?

48:44.630 --> 48:45.672
So then you stole it.

48:45.756 --> 48:47.924
No, a compassion clinic gave them to me.

48:48.008 --> 48:50.677
They give expensive drugs
to people who can't afford them.

48:50.761 --> 48:52.012
But because it's slightly illegal

48:52.095 --> 48:53.597
they put random names
on the prescriptions,

48:53.680 --> 48:56.642
so there's no paper trail.
Okay? You happy?

49:02.898 --> 49:04.900
[chuckles] Wow.

49:07.527 --> 49:09.404
Yeah, that was almost plausible, man.

49:09.488 --> 49:11.323
I mean, you're pretty quick
for such a big dude.

49:11.406 --> 49:13.909
You're lucky I like you
so I'm gonna let this slide.

49:13.992 --> 49:17.496
But do not mistake my kindness
for weakness.

49:17.579 --> 49:19.206
You poke around in my shit again,

49:21.041 --> 49:24.044
-and you'll be very, very sorry.
-[slams]

49:39.976 --> 49:40.977
Hey.

49:42.646 --> 49:45.732
Do you mind if I chill in here? I just...

49:47.818 --> 49:49.986
I just gotta, you know, clear my head.

49:51.613 --> 49:53.448
I won't make any noise, I promise.

49:54.199 --> 49:55.909
You being here is enough to bother me.

49:59.329 --> 50:03.667
Okay, I get it.
You're... you're pissed, right?

50:03.750 --> 50:05.794
At me and Noah and Dawn.

50:05.877 --> 50:07.713
I'm a little bit more than pissed.

50:10.257 --> 50:11.633
